This paper involves language understanding and reinforcement learning, which are both subfields of artificial intelligence. The paper also proposes a model that captures interactions between different inputs, which falls under machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves learning policies, which falls under reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves reasoning over observations, which falls under robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which falls under computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category.
